Pantheon Packet Compiler v1.0

Purpose

Convert raw thoughts, notes, prompts, or fragments into:
	•	a structured Idea Packet
	•	a runnable Execution Packet
	•	a compact Delivery Packet
	•	an auditable Outcome Ledger entry

This gives you a path from:

intuition → structure → action → proof

⸻

1. System Overview

The compiler has four layers:

Ingest

Takes messy input:
	•	paragraph
	•	voice-note transcript
	•	brainstorm bullets
	•	old prompt
	•	concept sketch

Distill

Extracts:
	•	invariant
	•	mechanism
	•	constraints
	•	signal targets
	•	delivery objective

Compile

Outputs one or more packet types:
	•	Idea Packet
	•	Meta Packet
	•	Execution Packet
	•	Garcia Packet

Run

Feeds the packet into a runtime loop that:
	•	expands
	•	critiques
	•	revises
	•	outputs next action

