2. Packet Types

A. Idea Packet

Used to store and rehydrate a concept.

packet_type: idea
id: IP-YYYYMMDD-001
title: ""
core_invariant: ""
mechanism: []
constraints: []
domains: []
signals_to_watch: []
failure_modes: []
ethical_boundary: ""
confidence: 0.0
timestamp: ""

B. Meta Packet

Used to describe how packets should combine, mutate, or expand.

packet_type: meta
id: MP-YYYYMMDD-001
goal: ""
input_packet_types: []
transforms:
  - compress
  - recombine
  - invert
  - stress_test
  - operationalize
output_target: ""
quality_bar:
  coherence: ""
  novelty: ""
  reversibility: ""
  usefulness: ""

C. Execution Packet

Used to turn an idea into a build or deployment plan.

packet_type: execution
id: XP-YYYYMMDD-001
objective: ""
success_metric: ""
resources_required: []
tasks:
  - id: T1
    description: ""
    owner: ""
    dependency: []
    output: ""
risks: []
deadline_mode: ""
next_action: ""

D. Garcia Packet

Used for “take the letter and deliver it” work. This is the action packet.

packet_type: garcia
id: GP-YYYYMMDD-001
mission: ""
