3. Compiler Pipeline

Stage 1 — Parse

Input:

rough text or notes

Output:
	•	nouns, verbs, relations
	•	central claim
	•	intended outcome
	•	ambiguities

Stage 2 — Extract Invariants

Questions:
	•	What must remain true?
	•	What is the mechanism?
	•	What cannot be violated?
	•	What changes with context?

Stage 3 — Select Packet Class

Rules:
	•	store concept → Idea Packet
	•	define transformations → Meta Packet
	•	move to implementation → Execution Packet
	•	move to outcome delivery → Garcia Packet

Stage 4 — Stress Test

Compiler checks for:
	•	vagueness
	•	hidden assumptions
	•	missing metric
	•	incoherent mechanism
	•	ethical violations
	•	non-falsifiable claims

Stage 5 — Emit

Return:
	•	compiled packet
	•	confidence
	•	missing variables
	•	recommended next runtime

⸻

4. Pantheon Runtime Loop

This is the OS behavior layer.

Runtime phases

Boot

Load:
	•	active packets
	•	mission priority
	•	constraints
	•	current context

Expand

Rehydrate packet into:
	•	explanation
	•	design
	•	plan
	•	artifact draft

Adversarial pass

Ask:
	•	what breaks?
	•	what is missing?
	•	what is unverifiable?
	•	what would make this fail in practice?

Recompile

Fold lessons back into packet.

Emit next action

Always produce:
	•	one concrete move
	•	one proof condition
	•	one checkpoint

